  <summary>2/10/1999--Introduced.
Directs the President, acting through the Office of Management and Budget and the Office of Personnel Management, to take necessary actions (including reduction-in-force actions) to ensure that the number of executive branch political appointments does not exceed 2,000 during any fiscal year after FY 2000.</summary>
